OL,3,CFly-tipping cases jump nearly 10% in a
OL,4,Cyear to new highs, council data shows
OL,6,FDrone of the Kidlington waste from the
OL,7,FEnvironment Agency
OL,9,FFly-tipping incidents in England have
OL,10,Frisen by 9% in a year, according to
OL,11,Fthe Department for Environment Food &
OL,12,FRural Affairs (DEFRA).
OL,14,FLocal authorities in England recorded
OL,15,Fa 9% rise in fly-tipping incidents in
OL,16,F2024/2025 from the 1.15 million they
OL,17,Fhad to deal with in 2023/2024.
OL,19,FIt marks the highest figures since new
OL,20,Fmethods for recording cases were
OL,21,Fintroduced in 2018/2019.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
