OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1772107375
OL,3,CFly-tipping cases jump nearly 10% in a
OL,4,Cyear to new highs, council data shows
OL,6,FFly-tipping vehicles face being
OL,7,Fsearched, seized, and destroyed under
OL,8,Fnew government guidance in response to
OL,9,Frising incidents across the country.
OL,11,FLocal authorities dealt with 1.26
OL,12,Fmillion incidents last year, compared
OL,13,Fto 1.15 million in 2023/24, with 62%
OL,14,Fof fly-tipping incidents involving
OL,15,Fhousehold waste.
OL,17,FIn 31% of these cases, a "small van
OL,18,Fload" of waste was dumped, making it
OL,19,Fthe most common quantity category for
OL,20,Ffly-tipping.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1772107375
OL,3,CFly-tipping cases jump nearly 10% in a
OL,4,Cyear to new highs, council data shows
OL,6,FWhile the number of fixed penalty
OL,7,Fnotices also increased by 9% in the
OL,8,Fpast year, the total number of court
OL,9,Ffines decreased by 9% in 2024/25.
OL,11,FWith the majority of fly-tipping
OL,12,Fincidents coming from household waste,
OL,13,Fjust over a quarter of those are from
OL,14,Fblack bags.
OL,16,FThe rest is defined as "other" waste
OL,17,Fby Defra which may include material
OL,18,Ffrom house or shed clearances, old
OL,19,Ffurniture, carpets and the waste from
OL,20,Fsmall scale DIY works.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1772107375
OL,3,CFly-tipping cases jump nearly 10% in a
OL,4,Cyear to new highs, council data shows
OL,6,FThe number of fly-tipping incidents by
OL,7,Fsize indicates household waste may be
OL,8,Fbeing dumped on a large scale. Around
OL,9,F381,000 of the incidents amounted to
OL,10,Fthe size of a small van load, while
OL,11,F327,000 were a car boot or less.
OL,13,FThese figures were much higher than
OL,14,Fsingle item incidents (201,000) and
OL,15,Fsingle black bags (102,000). All types
OL,16,Fof fly-tipping mentioned above have
OL,17,Frisen in the past year.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
