CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1772107375
OL,3,CFly-tipping cases jump nearly 10% in a
OL,4,Cyear to new highs, council data shows
OL,6,FThe only other region of England above
OL,7,Fthe national average was the North
OL,8,FEast, whose numbers had marginally
OL,9,Fdropped from 25 to 24.
OL,11,FThe South West was the best performing
OL,12,Fregion, remaining at nine incidents
OL,13,Fper 1,000 people.
OL,15,FWhat is being done about it?
OL,17,FThe government hopes their new
OL,18,Fmeasures will increase the money
OL,19,Fraised from fly-tipping funds which is
OL,20,Fring-fenced by councils to clean up
OL,21,Fland impacted by waste dumping.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
